6.22	Renuka	Renuka	Renuka or Yellamma of the fallen, in the Hindu pantheon. Yellamma is a patron goddess of rural folk of Karnataka and Andhra Pradesh. Her devotees have revered her as the "Mother of the Universe" or Jagadamba. Legends say that Yellamma is the incarnation of Kali, who on one hand symbolizes the death of ego, and on the other hand is the mother who is compassionate about her children.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fb/Goddess_Renuka-mata_of_Mahur_%28Maharashtra%29.jpg/200px-Goddess_Renuka-mata_of_Mahur_%28Maharashtra%29.jpg
